  "stage": {
    "id": "stage_1_foundations",
    "stageNumber": 1,
    "title": "Stage 1: Foundations",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "attention_mechanism",
        "title": "What is Attention?",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Selective focus on input\n- Weighted importance scores\n- Context-aware computation\n\nAttention lets models focus on the most relevant parts of the input. Imagine reading a sentence in a foreign language — you'd zoom in on key words and skim less important ones. That's what attention does.",
        "position": {
          "x": 5,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "self_attention",
        "title": "Self-Attention: Looking Within",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Intra-sequence relationships\n- Each position attends to all others\n- Parallel computation\n\nSelf-attention lets each word look at every other word in the sentence simultaneously. It's like everyone in a group chat can see everyone else's messages at once, enabling rich interdependencies.",
        "position": {
          "x": 9,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "residual_layer_norm",
        "title": "Residual Connections & Layer Norm",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Skip connections\n- Training stability\n- Gradient flow\n\nDeep networks suffer when gradients shrink layer-by-layer. Residual connections bypass layers, letting gradients flow directly. Layer norm stabilizes this flow. Together they're like safety railings on a steep staircase.",
        "position": {
          "x": 13,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-1",
      "question": "When stacking many layers in a neural network, what problem do skip connections (residual paths) help solve? (1) Reduce memory (2) Prevent vanishing gradients (3) Speed up inference.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "options": [
        "Reduce memory",
        "Prevent vanishing gradients",
        "Speed up inference"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Prevent vanishing gradients",
      "position": {
        "x": 18,
        "y": 7
      }
    },
